In this statement, President Barack Obama reaffirms the United States' commitment to the principles outlined in the United Nations Convention Against Torture. He emphasizes that torture is never justified and goes against US and international law, as well as human dignity. Obama states that the US will not engage in torture and will stand against it wherever it occurs. He highlights his administration's actions against torture, including issuing an executive order prohibiting torture and providing support for groups working to rehabilitate torture victims. Obama also expresses the US's commitment to cooperating with governments and civil society organizations globally to fight against torture.